  "cards": [
    {
      "id": "s1-0",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Usage",
      "body": "The default behavior is to run a new command with a given affinity mask\n\n```shell\n$ taskset [mask] [command] [arguments]\n```"
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-2",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Usage #2",
      "body": "```shell\n$ taskset -p [pid]\n```\n\n```shell\n$ taskset -p [mask] [pid]\n```\n\nYou can also retrieve the CPU affinity of an existing task"
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-4",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Common Options",
      "body": "| Command | Alternavite | Meaning                                                                                                                                                  |\n| ------- | ----------- | -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |\n| `-a`    | --all-tasks | Set or retrieve the CPU affinity of all the task (threads) for a given PID.                                                                              |\n| `-c`    | --cpu-list  | Interpret mask as numerical list of processors instead of a bitmask.</br>Numbers are separated by commas and may include ranges. For example: `0,5,8-11` |\n| `-p`    | --pid       | Operate on an existing PID and do not launch a new task.                                                                                                 |\n| `-h`    | --help      | Display help text and exit.                                                                                                                              |\n| `-v`    | --version   | Print version and exit.                                                                                                                                  |"
    },
    {
      "id": "s2-5",
      "sectionId": "s2",
      "title": "View%20CPU%20Affinity",
      "body": "%60%60%60shell%0A%24%20taskset%20-cp%2029523%0Apid%2029523's%20current%20affinity%20list%3A%200-15%0A%60%60%60%0A%0AThat%20mean%20process%20with%20PID%20%6029523%60%20is%20active%20on%20CPU%20range%20from%20%60%5B0%2C1%2C...%2C15%5D%60%20which%20means%20%6016%60%20total.%0A%0A**PID**%3A%20Process%20Identifier%20-%20is%20a%20unique%20numerical%20identifier%20given%20to%20each%20running%20process%2C%20you%20can%20view%20PID%20of%0Aprocesses%20in%20%60top%60%20or%20%60htop%60%20tools%0A%0A_If%20you%20run%20the%20above%20command%20but%20get%20the%20message%20%60bad%20usage%60%2C%20try%20with%20PID%20%3D%201_%0A%0A%60%60%60shell%0A%24%20taskset%20-cp%201%0A%60%60%60",
      "encoded": true
    },
    {
      "id": "s2-10",
      "sectionId": "s2",
      "title": "Set%20CPU%20Affinity",
      "body": "Now%20let's%20try%20to%20set%20process%20in%20to%20a%20specify%20CPU.%20For%20example%2C%20we%20have%20a%20process%20has%20PID%20%3D%2014846%0A%0ALet's%20see%20the%20CPU%20affinity%20list%20of%20this%20process%20first%3A%0A%0A%60%60%60shell%0A%24%20taskset%20-cp%2014846%0Apid%2014846's%20current%20affinity%20list%3A%200-15%0A%60%60%60",
      "encoded": true
    },
    {
      "id": "s2-13",
      "sectionId": "s2",
      "title": "Change%20CPU%20affinity%20to%201%3A",
      "body": "%60%60%60shell%0A%24%20taskset%20-cp%201%2014846%0Apid%2014846's%20current%20affinity%20list%3A%200-15%0Apid%2014846's%20new%20affinity%20list%3A%201%0A%60%60%60%0A%0AAs%20we%20see%2C%20CPU%20affinity%20was%20changed",
      "encoded": true
    },
    {
      "id": "s2-15",
      "sectionId": "s2",
      "title": "Set%20CPU%20Affinity%20with%20multiple%20value",
      "body": "That%20mean%20new%20CPU%20affinity%20list%20is%20%60%5B0%2C1%2C2%2C3%5D%60%0A%0A%60%60%60shell%0A%24%20taskset%20-cp%200-3%2014846%0Apid%2014846's%20current%20affinity%20list%3A%201%0Apid%2014846's%20new%20affinity%20list%3A%200-3%0A%60%60%60%0A%0AYou%20can%20set%20single%20CPU%20with%20the%20following%20command%3A%0A%0A%60%60%60shell%0A%24%20taskset%20-cp%205%2C8%2C12%2014846%0Apid%2014846's%20current%20affinity%20list%3A%200-3%0Apid%2014846's%20new%20affinity%20list%3A%205%2C8%2C12%0A%60%60%60%0A%0AThat%20mean%20new%20CPU%20affinity%20list%20is%20%60%5B5%2C8%2C12%5D%60",
      "encoded": true
    },
    {
      "id": "s2-20",
      "sectionId": "s2",
      "title": "Other",
      "body": "You%20can%20set%20affinity%20by%20range%20with%20other%20like%20a%20specify%20CPU%0A%0A%60%60%60shell%0A%24%20taskset%20-cp%201-3%2C12%2014846%0A%60%60%60%0A%0AOr%0A%0A%60%60%60shell%0A%24%20taskset%20-cp%201-6%3A2%2014846%0A%60%60%60%0A%0AThe%20suffix%20%22%3AN%22%20specifies%20stride%20in%20the%20range%2C%20for%20example%200-10%3A3%20is%20interpreted%20as%200%2C3%2C6%2C9%20list.",
      "encoded": true
    },
